<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">377. Hepler, Donald E., Cecil Howard Jensen, and Paul I. Wallach. Interior Design Fundamentals. New York: McGraw-Hill, 1983. 374 pp. Index, glossary, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-07-028296-X. </p><p class="annot">This basic text for interior design students begins with a thorough treatment of the principles and elements of design. This is followed by information specific to space planning, surface treatment, furniture, and equipment, and a concluding section on the profession. The discussion of color examines the spectrum, color characteristics of hue, value, and intensity, traditional color harmonies, and color effects, including a mention of the relationship between color and light. Though brief, the color section is clear and well illustrated. </p></div>
